.SH NAME
HTMLTextAreaElement.select_event \- HTMLTextAreaElement: select event
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]select\f[B]\f[R] event fires when some text has been
selected.
.SH SYNTAX
Use the event name in methods like \f[CR]addEventListener()\f[R], or set
an event handler property.
.IP
.EX
addEventListener(\(dqselect\(dq, (event) => { })

onselect = (event) => { }
.EE
.SH EVENT TYPE
A generic \f[CR]Event\f[R].
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS Selection logger
.IP
.EX
<\f[B]textarea\f[R]>Try selecting some text in this element.</\f[B]textarea\f[R]>
<\f[B]p\f[R] id=\(dqlog\(dq></\f[B]p\f[R]>
.EE
.IP
.EX
\f[B]function\f[R] logSelection(event) {
  \f[B]const\f[R] log = document.getElementById(\(dqlog\(dq);
  \f[B]const\f[R] selection = event.target.value.substring(
    event.target.selectionStart,
    event.target.selectionEnd,
  );
  log.textContent = \(gaYou selected: ${selection}\(ga;
}

\f[B]const\f[R] textarea = document.querySelector(\(dqtextarea\(dq);
textarea.addEventListener(\(dqselect\(dq, logSelection);
.EE
.SS onselect equivalent
You can also set up the event handler using the \f[CR]onselect\f[R]
property:
.IP
.EX
textarea.onselect = logSelection;
.EE
